  <item>
    <title><![CDATA[Inside Our Douala Production Workflow]]></title>
    <link><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/inside-our-douala-production-workflow/]]></link>
    <pubDate>Tue, 07 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
    <dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
    <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/inside-our-douala-production-workflow/]]></guid>
    <description></description>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Every garment begins with digital pattern drafting, where fit, proportion, and movement are modeled before cutting starts. This stage reduces waste and improves precision.</p><p>After cutting, materials move to artisan finishing where signature details are applied by hand. This includes embroidery accents, trims, and selective surface treatments.</p><p>Final quality control combines visual checks and wear simulation. By the time a piece reaches customers, it has passed both engineering standards and craft standards.</p>]]></content:encoded>
    <excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[A behind-the-scenes look at how Diensa pieces move from sketch to finished garment.]]></excerpt:encoded>
