  <item>
    <title><![CDATA[The Rise of Structured Feminine Silhouettes]]></title>
    <link><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/rise-of-structured-feminine-silhouettes/]]></link>
    <pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
    <dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
    <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/rise-of-structured-feminine-silhouettes/]]></guid>
    <description></description>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Today’s women’s tailoring is moving toward intentional structure—defined shoulders, sculpted waists, and balanced volume. This does not remove softness; it frames it.</p><p>Our design direction uses measured construction to support movement rather than restrict it. We combine support fabrics with flowing layers to create confidence in motion.</p><p>The appeal is clear: pieces that communicate authority while remaining elegant, breathable, and wearable from morning meetings to evening events.</p>]]></content:encoded>
    <excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[How stronger lines and softer drape are shaping a powerful new womenswear identity.]]></excerpt:encoded>
