  <item>
    <title><![CDATA[From Concept to Collection: 6-Week Sprint]]></title>
    <link><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/from-concept-to-collection-6-week-sprint/]]></link>
    <pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
    <dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
    <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/from-concept-to-collection-6-week-sprint/]]></guid>
    <description></description>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Week 1 starts with theme definition, reference mapping, and technical constraints. Clear direction at this stage prevents expensive redesigns later.</p><p>Weeks 2 to 4 are dedicated to prototyping, fit revisions, and material finalization. We test each piece for comfort, durability, and style coherence.</p><p>Weeks 5 and 6 focus on pre-production and launch readiness. With disciplined checkpoints, a six-week sprint can produce a collection that feels deliberate—not rushed.</p>]]></content:encoded>
    <excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[A practical timeline showing how a focused team can launch a refined capsule quickly.]]></excerpt:encoded>
