  <item>
    <title><![CDATA[Sustainable Fabric Choices That Actually Scale]]></title>
    <link><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/sustainable-fabric-choices-that-actually-scale/]]></link>
    <pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
    <dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
    <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/sustainable-fabric-choices-that-actually-scale/]]></guid>
    <description></description>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Many sustainable initiatives fail because they ignore supply realities. We prioritize fabrics that can be sourced responsibly and replenished consistently.</p><p>Our material strategy focuses on traceable cotton blends, low-impact dye processes, and predictable lead times. This supports both environmental goals and delivery commitments.</p><p>True sustainability in fashion is operational. It is built into sourcing calendars, production planning, and long-term supplier relationships.</p>]]></content:encoded>
    <excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[Sustainability works best when material choices are both ethical and production-ready.]]></excerpt:encoded>
