    <title><![CDATA[Designing for Heat: Luxury in Tropical Climates]]></title>
    <link><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/designing-for-heat-luxury-in-tropical-climates/]]></link>
    <pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
    <dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
    <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[https://diensabyansah.com/designing-for-heat-luxury-in-tropical-climates/]]></guid>
    <description></description>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Tropical luxury is about engineering comfort without sacrificing elegance. Fabric weight, seam placement, and ventilation zones become core design decisions.</p><p>We prioritize breathable fibers and looser air channels while preserving sharp visual lines. Strategic paneling keeps garments polished and practical in warm conditions.</p><p>The result is clothing designed for real climates and real movement—an approach that should become standard in global fashion design.</p>]]></content:encoded>
    <excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[Breathable luxury requires smarter cuts, lighter layers, and climate-aware materials.]]></excerpt:encoded>
